sentences.english: He spread a net for my feet and turned me back.
sentences.chinese: 他铺下网罗，绊我的脚，使我转回。

sentences.english: Ahsoka looked up shortly, her gaze bouncing back from the white armoured back like a thief.
sentences.chinese: 阿索卡将视线转回白甲背影，小偷似的瞄了一下。

sentences.english: The above example jumps back to the beginning of a file. If you don't want to go back quite all the way -- let's say a kilobyte into it -- then you just write
sentences.chinese: 以上示例将跳转回文件的开头。

sentences.english: Those who enter the PhD Program without a master degree may return to the Master Program upon the approval of the Institute Faculty Meeting.
sentences.chinese: 迳修读博士班者，经务会议同意，可转回硕士班就读。

sentences.english: Return to your test page and try to drop the button onto the column tag again.
sentences.chinese: 转回至测试页面，并再次尝试将按钮拖到列标签上。

sentences.english: They return at evening: they make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.
sentences.chinese: 他们晚上转回，叫号如狗，围城绕行。

sentences.english: None who go to her return or attain the paths of life.
sentences.chinese: 凡到她那里去的不得转回，也得不着生命的路。

sentences.english: What satirizes , this regeneration punctured the human to return the vision Holland.
sentences.chinese: 讽刺的是，这回热刺人又把目光转回了荷兰。

sentences.english: Eli returns and Teri hides the phone again.
sentences.chinese: 伊菜又折转回木屋中来，泰瑞也再次将手机藏了起来。

sentences.english: When they turned back into the wilderness they found none.
sentences.chinese: 当他们转回往旷野去的时候，就没有了。

sentences.english: Truth Is Lacking, And Whoever Turns From Evil Is Despoiled.
sentences.chinese: 真相越来越少，而那些个从邪恶里转回的人被掠夺了。

sentences.english: None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.
sentences.chinese: 凡到他那里去的不得转回，也得不着生命的路。

sentences.english: There would be a loud "thud", and then he would swerve back on the road.
sentences.chinese: 听到“砰“的一声之后他再转回路上正常行驶。

sentences.english: The soldierglanced at her quickly and then looked back to his papers.
sentences.chinese: 那个士兵很快地瞥了他一眼，然后目光转回他的文件。

sentences.english: She returned her attention to the sand sea.
They return at evening, snarling like dogs, and prowl about the city.
sentences.chinese: 他们晚上转回，叫号如狗，围城绕行。
